# What is Git?

Git is a Distributed Version Control System (DVCS).

It tracks changes in source code and allows multiple developers to work on the same project.

---

# What is GitHub?

GitHub is a cloud-based platform used to host Git repositories.

It allows developers to collaborate, share code, and maintain version history.

---

# Git vs GitHub

| Git | GitHub |
|------|---------|
| Version Control System | Cloud Hosting Platform |
| Installed on Local Computer | Works on the Internet |
| Tracks Code Changes | Stores Git Repositories |
| Can Work Without GitHub | Uses Git |

---

# Repository

A Repository (Repo) is a project folder tracked by Git.

Types:

- Local Repository
- Remote Repository

---

# Local Repository

Repository stored on your computer.

---

# Remote Repository

