# Common Interview Mistakes

❌ Git and GitHub are the same.

✅ Git is a Version Control System.

GitHub is a Cloud Hosting Platform.

---

❌ Commit uploads files to GitHub.

✅ Commit saves changes locally.

Push uploads them.

---

❌ Pull and Clone are the same.

✅ Clone copies a repository for the first time.

Pull updates an existing repository.

---

# Revision Box

✅ Git → Version Control

✅ GitHub → Cloud Repository

✅ Commit → Local Snapshot

✅ Push → Upload Changes

✅ Pull → Download Changes

✅ Clone → Copy Repository

✅ Branch → Separate Development

✅ Merge → Combine Branches

